<subSubSection id="4FF0F1E8FF53FF19A7ADFAE7FE50DA27" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0755A263FF53FF19A7ADFAE7FEF0D923" blockId="202.[189,310,1288,1314]" box="[189,310,1288,1314]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">
<heading id="5C1D150FFF53FF19A7ADFAE7FEF0D923" bold="true" box="[189,310,1288,1314]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" reason="3">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF53FF19A7ADFAE7FEF0D923" bold="true" box="[189,310,1288,1314]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF53FF19A7ADFAD7FD3DD9BE" blockId="202.[189,1399,1336,1471]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">
This species may be separated from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="C0EAD9E0FF53FF19A444FAD7FC5ED953" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[852,920,1336,1362]" class="Arachnida" family="Charinidae" genus="Sarax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amblypygi" pageId="202" pageNumber="203" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="359E7E71FF53FF19A444FAD7FC5ED953" box="[852,920,1336,1362]" italics="true" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">Sarax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Southeast Asia and Oceania by the following combination of characters: uniform coloration without distinct stripes; female genital plaque flattened posteromedially; basal segment of chelicera with tooth on retrolateral surface, opposite to bifid tooth; leg IV basitibia with three pseudo-articles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0755A263FF53FF19A7ADFA07FE50DA27" blockId="202.[189,1399,1511,1574]" pageId="202" pageNumber="203">
